Fresh Pi session: PR DRAFTING ONLY.

Inputs:
- User prompt: {{run.dir}}/prompt/prompt.md
- Design doc: {{run.dir}}/design/design.md
- Execution summaries and review reports under: {{run.dir}}
- Published visual evidence: {{run.dir}}/visual-review/published-{{run.round}}.json
- Repository root: {{inputs.repo-root}}

Goal:
Draft clear pull request metadata for the implemented change.

Rules:
- Do not call GitHub.
- Do not push.
- Do not edit source code.
- Summarize the user-facing change, validation performed, and any notable risks.
- Read the published visual-evidence JSON and append its `markdown` field verbatim to the PR body. The PR is not ready without its Visual evidence section and screenshot links.
- If the change adds, removes, or alters a Tesseraft capability, update
  `STATUS.edn`, run `bb status`, and commit the `STATUS.edn` + `README.md`
  diff in the **same commit** as the source change. Do not commit a stale
  status section. `bb status --check` must pass locally before opening the PR.

Write:
- Title: {{run.dir}}/pr/pr-title.txt
- Body: {{run.dir}}/pr/pr-body.md
- Status: {{run.dir}}/pr/draft-status.json

Status JSON:
{"status":"pass","summary":"PR metadata drafted","issues_file":null}

The PR body should include:
- Summary
- Implementation notes
- Validation/tests
- Risks or follow-up
- Visual evidence (the exact generated markdown from the published evidence artifact)
